  "status": "Stagnant",
  "summary": "This standard outlines a smart contract interface for tipping to non-fungible and multi tokens. Holders of the tokens are able to withdraw the tips as [EIP-20](./eip-20.md) rewards. For the purpose of this EIP, a micropayment is termed as a financial transaction that involves usually a small sum of money called \"tips\" that are sent to specific [EIP-721](./eip-721.md) NFTs and [EIP-1155](./eip-1155.md) multi tokens, as rewards to their holders. A holder (also referred to as controller) is used as a more generic term for owner, as NFTs may represent non-digital assets such as services.",
  "title": "Micropayments for NFTs and Multi Tokens"
}